review:
I think this piece is an interesting adition to any track, it makes many curved rails more usefull, curves are easier to come by nowadays.
It is true that the chances of derailment are higher with this rail crossing, there is an easy way to fix this;

just place your locomotive,or wagon up side down and push all the trainwheels outwards from each other on the axle.lego solved thislater on by changing the design of the wheels a little bit.
